Caswell walked across the room to the therapeutic machine. One hand was still in his jacket pocket; the other he laid affectionately upon the Regenerator. \par
"The poor thing tried its best," he said. "Of course, it couldn't cure what wasn't there." He laughed. "But it came very near succeeding!" \line\line\par
\pard\sb100\sa100\qc\'b7 \'b7 \'b7 \'b7 \'b7 \par
\pard\sb100\sa100\line\line Rath studied Caswell's face and said, in a trained, casual tone, "Glad there was no harm, sir. The Company will, of course, reimburse you for your lost time and for your mental anguish\emdash " \par
